    "-The base right of income >50k is about 3x higher for men than for women, which already reflects historical wage inequalities. \n",
    "\n",
    "-So, any classifier that is trained on this imbalanced data without any intervention will probably reproduce or amplify these disparities. \n",
    "\n",
    "**The fairness question is not whether disparities exist (clearly, they do), but how the model should be evaluated and whose judgment determines what counts as acceptable.**\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the moment in the audit where the choice of auditor really matters. An internal team focused on accuracy may treat the base-rate disparity as \"ground truth\" since they care about accuracy. An external auditor that is more focused on stakeholder engagement may treat these results as evidence that fairness *cannot* be reduced to predictive accuracy alone.\n"
   ]
