    "## 3. MEASURE: Baseline Classifier and Fairness Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "The MEASURE function evaluates the trained model along multiple dimensions: overall performance, disaggregated performance across protected groups, and fairness-specific metrics. We use **Fairlearn's `MetricFrame`** for disaggregated views and **AIF360's `ClassificationMetric`** for disparate impact and statistical parity difference.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Train/Test Split and Baseline Model\n",
    "Predict whether a person (split by sex) makes more than 50k a year (high earner) using a simple logistic regression model on the UCI data, and compute performance metrics (accuracy and Area under ROC Curve, which measures false positive vs. true positive rate). \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "f99c2a26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Overall accuracy: 0.847\n",
      "Overall AUC:      0.902\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Split using AIF360 to preserve sensitive attribute alignment\n",
    "adult_train, adult_test = adult.split([0.7], shuffle=True, seed=42) #split data into 70% training, 30% test \n",
    "\n",
    "X_train = adult_train.features\n",
    "y_train = adult_train.labels.ravel() #flatten labels from 2D--> 1D array \n",
    "X_test = adult_test.features\n",
    "y_test = adult_test.labels.ravel()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sensitive attribute (sex): 1 = Male (privileged), 0 = Female (unprivileged)\n",
    "sex_idx = adult_train.feature_names.index('sex') #save sensitive value separately so we can view the model's predictions separately by sex\n",
    "sens_train = X_train[:, sex_idx]\n",
    "sens_test = X_test[:, sex_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardize features\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler() #ensure features are on the same numerical scale (17-90 for age vs 10000s for capital gain), so they can be evaluated fairly\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Baseline logistic regression\n",
    "clf = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42) \n",
    "#use logistic regression instead of neural network because it is simple and interpretable, which is what we want for a fairness audit.\n",
    "clf.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "y_score = clf.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Overall accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Overall AUC:      {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_score):.3f}\") \n",
    "#^^^How well does the model separate the two groups? AUC = 1.0 means perfect separation, AUC = 0.5 means no separation (random guessing)"
   ]
  },
