    "### 3.5 Internal vs. External Interpretation of the Same Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "The numbers above are mathematically unambiguous. Their interpretation, however, depends on the auditor.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Metric | What an internal team might say | What an external auditor might say |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Overall accuracy ~0.85** | \"The model is accurate! Deploy it.\" | \"Overall accuracy does not show which subgroup absorbs the errors.\" |\n",
    "| **Selection rate disparity** (Male ~26%, Female ~10%) | \"This reflects real base-rate differences in the training data.\" | \"The model is offering fewer positive predictions to women regardless of merit, which amplifies the disparity.\" |\n",
    "| **Disparate impact ~0.35** | \"Although it is below the 0.8 four-fifths threshold, the underlying base rates differ, which we can't fix.\" | \"Disparate impact this severe would not survive an EEOC employment-discrimination challenge.\" |\n",
    "| **Equal opportunity difference** | \"The TPR gap is small, so qualified women are still being identified.\" | \"Even a small TPR gap, applied at scale, denies opportunity to thousands of qualified individuals.\" |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9669c62f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. MANAGE: Mitigation Strategies and Re-Measurement\n",
    "\n",
    "The MANAGE function applies risk-treatment strategies from both repositories and re-evaluates the system. We apply 2 mitigations of different types:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Reweighing (AIF360, preprocessing)** adjusts training-instance weights so that the protected attribute and outcome become statistically independent in the training distribution. The model itself is unchanged; only the data weights are.\n",
    "2. **Threshold Optimization (Fairlearn, postprocessing)** keeps the model fixed but learns separate decision thresholds per group to satisfy a specified fairness constraint. Here we use demographic parity as the constraint.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.1 Mitigation 1: Reweighing (AIF360)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "354f31f8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "After Reweighing:\n",
